cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with enhancing the visual fidelity of surgical simulations using style transfer, which involves manipulating images and videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves graphics and visualization, which falls under cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of simulation in surgical education, which could be categorized under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also involves multimedia processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the possibility of extending the technique to different applications, which could be categorized under cs.RO (Robotics).
